{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1200,"text":"Democracy."},{"time":2960,"text":"In the West,"},{"time":4320,"text":"we make a colossal mistake\ntaking it for granted."},{"time":8280,"text":"We see democracy"},{"time":9600,"text":"not as the most fragile\nof flowers that it really is,"},{"time":14120,"text":"but we see it as part\nof our society's furniture."},{"time":17960,"text":"We tend to think of it\nas an intransigent given."},{"time":22680,"text":"We mistakenly believe that capitalism\nbegets inevitably democracy."},{"time":27920,"text":"It doesn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29280,"text":"Singapore's Lee Kuan Yew\nand his great imitators in Beijing"},{"time":33680,"text":"have demonstrated beyond reasonable doubt"},{"time":36640,"text":"that it is perfectly possible\nto have a flourishing capitalism,"},{"time":40560,"text":"spectacular growth,"},{"time":42960,"text":"while politics remains democracy-free."},{"time":46040,"text":"Indeed, democracy is receding\nin our neck of the woods,"},{"time":50480,"text":"here in Europe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52080,"text":"Earlier this year,\nwhile I was representing Greece --"},{"time":55480,"text":"the newly elected Greek government --"},{"time":58240,"text":"in the Eurogroup as its Finance Minister,"},{"time":60960,"text":"I was told in no uncertain terms\nthat our nation's democratic process --"},{"time":65920,"text":"our elections --"},{"time":67360,"text":"could not be allowed to interfere"},{"time":69160,"text":"with economic policies\nthat were being implemented in Greece."},{"time":73120,"text":"At that moment,"},{"time":74360,"text":"I felt that there could be no greater\nvindication of Lee Kuan Yew,"},{"time":78680,"text":"or the Chinese Communist Party,"},{"time":80240,"text":"indeed of some recalcitrant\nfriends of mine who kept telling me"},{"time":84000,"text":"that democracy would be banned\nif it ever threatened to change anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89640,"text":"Tonight, here, I want to present to you"},{"time":92920,"text":"an economic case\nfor an authentic democracy."},{"time":96600,"text":"I want to ask you\nto join me in believing again"},{"time":101480,"text":"that Lee Kuan Yew,"},{"time":104480,"text":"the Chinese Communist Party"},{"time":105880,"text":"and indeed the Eurogroup"},{"time":107280,"text":"are wrong in believing\nthat we can dispense with democracy --"},{"time":111600,"text":"that we need an authentic,\nboisterous democracy."},{"time":115360,"text":"And without democracy,"},{"time":118360,"text":"our societies will be nastier,"},{"time":121240,"text":"our future bleak"},{"time":123400,"text":"and our great, new technologies wasted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126240,"text":"Speaking of waste,"},{"time":127520,"text":"allow me to point out\nan interesting paradox"},{"time":130320,"text":"that is threatening\nour economies as we speak."},{"time":133120,"text":"I call it the twin peaks paradox."},{"time":135440,"text":"One peak you understand --"},{"time":136760,"text":"you know it, you recognize it --"},{"time":138400,"text":"is the mountain of debts\nthat has been casting a long shadow"},{"time":143480,"text":"over the United States,\nEurope, the whole world."},{"time":146320,"text":"We all recognize the mountain of debts."},{"time":148880,"text":"But few people discern its twin."},{"time":153640,"text":"A mountain of idle cash"},{"time":156840,"text":"belonging to rich savers\nand to corporations,"},{"time":161120,"text":"too terrified to invest it"},{"time":163720,"text":"into the productive activities\nthat can generate the incomes"},{"time":167040,"text":"from which you can extinguish\nthe mountain of debts"},{"time":170120,"text":"and which can produce all those things\nthat humanity desperately needs,"},{"time":174120,"text":"like green energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175800,"text":"Now let me give you two numbers."},{"time":178160,"text":"Over the last three months,"},{"time":179520,"text":"in the United States,\nin Britain and in the Eurozone,"},{"time":182320,"text":"we have invested, collectively,\n3.4 trillion dollars"},{"time":186760,"text":"on all the wealth-producing goods --"},{"time":189440,"text":"things like industrial plants, machinery,"},{"time":192480,"text":"office blocks, schools,"},{"time":194720,"text":"roads, railways, machinery,\nand so on and so forth."},{"time":197880,"text":"$3.4 trillion sounds like a lot of money"},{"time":200640,"text":"until you compare it to the $5.1 trillion"},{"time":204520,"text":"that has been slushing around\nin the same countries,"},{"time":207240,"text":"in our financial institutions,"},{"time":209080,"text":"doing absolutely nothing\nduring the same period"},{"time":213440,"text":"except inflating stock exchanges\nand bidding up house prices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218320,"text":"So a mountain of debt\nand a mountain of idle cash"},{"time":223600,"text":"form twin peaks, \nfailing to cancel each other out"},{"time":227320,"text":"through the normal\noperation of the markets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230160,"text":"The result is stagnant wages,"},{"time":233360,"text":"more than a quarter of 25- to 54-year-olds\nin America, in Japan and in Europe"},{"time":239040,"text":"out of work."},{"time":240560,"text":"And consequently, low aggregate demand,"},{"time":242920,"text":"which in a never-ending cycle,"},{"time":245160,"text":"reinforces the pessimism of the investors,"},{"time":248880,"text":"who, fearing low demand,\nreproduce it by not investing --"},{"time":252720,"text":"exactly like Oedipus' father,"},{"time":255440,"text":"who, terrified\nby the prophecy of the oracle"},{"time":257959,"text":"that his son would grow up to kill him,"},{"time":260720,"text":"unwittingly engineered the conditions"},{"time":262680,"text":"that ensured that Oedipus,\nhis son, would kill him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266560,"text":"This is my quarrel with capitalism."},{"time":269200,"text":"Its gross wastefulness,"},{"time":271240,"text":"all this idle cash,"},{"time":272880,"text":"should be energized to improve lives,"},{"time":277000,"text":"to develop human talents,"},{"time":278360,"text":"and indeed to finance\nall these technologies,"},{"time":281240,"text":"green technologies,"},{"time":282520,"text":"which are absolutely essential\nfor saving planet Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286280,"text":"Am I right in believing\nthat democracy might be the answer?"},{"time":289560,"text":"I believe so,"},{"time":290800,"text":"but before we move on,"},{"time":292040,"text":"what do we mean by democracy?"},{"time":294520,"text":"Aristotle defined democracy"},{"time":296960,"text":"as the constitution\nin which the free and the poor,"},{"time":301920,"text":"being in the majority, control government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"Now, of course Athenian democracy\nexcluded too many."},{"time":308320,"text":"Women, migrants and,\nof course, the slaves."},{"time":312040,"text":"But it would be a mistake"},{"time":313320,"text":"to dismiss the significance\nof ancient Athenian democracy"},{"time":316920,"text":"on the basis of whom it excluded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319680,"text":"What was more pertinent,"},{"time":320960,"text":"and continues to be so\nabout ancient Athenian democracy,"},{"time":324840,"text":"was the inclusion of the working poor,"},{"time":328360,"text":"who not only acquired\nthe right to free speech,"},{"time":333080,"text":"but more importantly, crucially,"},{"time":335360,"text":"they acquired the rights\nto political judgments"},{"time":338000,"text":"that were afforded equal weight"},{"time":340400,"text":"in the decision-making\nconcerning matters of state."},{"time":344080,"text":"Now, of course, Athenian\ndemocracy didn't last long."},{"time":347160,"text":"Like a candle that burns brightly,\nit burned out quickly."},{"time":351600,"text":"And indeed,"},{"time":352840,"text":"our liberal democracies today\ndo not have their roots in ancient Athens."},{"time":357120,"text":"They have their roots in the Magna Carta,"},{"time":359480,"text":"in the 1688 Glorious Revolution,"},{"time":362760,"text":"indeed in the American constitution."},{"time":365000,"text":"Whereas Athenian democracy\nwas focusing on the masterless citizen"},{"time":370040,"text":"and empowering the working poor,"},{"time":373240,"text":"our liberal democracies are founded\non the Magna Carta tradition,"},{"time":377440,"text":"which was, after all,\na charter for masters."},{"time":380560,"text":"And indeed, liberal democracy\nonly surfaced when it was possible"},{"time":384880,"text":"to separate fully the political sphere\nfrom the economic sphere,"},{"time":388760,"text":"so as to confine the democratic process\nfully in the political sphere,"},{"time":393840,"text":"leaving the economic sphere --"},{"time":395720,"text":"the corporate world, if you want --"},{"time":397680,"text":"as a democracy-free zone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401720,"text":"Now, in our democracies today,"},{"time":404720,"text":"this separation of the economic\nfrom the political sphere,"},{"time":408240,"text":"the moment it started happening,"},{"time":410520,"text":"it gave rise to an inexorable,\nepic struggle between the two,"},{"time":414840,"text":"with the economic sphere\ncolonizing the political sphere,"},{"time":418080,"text":"eating into its power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420480,"text":"Have you wondered why politicians\nare not what they used to be?"},{"time":424560,"text":"It's not because their DNA\nhas degenerated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":428640,"text":"It is rather because one can be\nin government today and not in power,"},{"time":433280,"text":"because power has migrated\nfrom the political to the economic sphere,"},{"time":436600,"text":"which is separate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439160,"text":"Indeed,"},{"time":440760,"text":"I spoke about my quarrel\nwith capitalism."},{"time":443080,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":444840,"text":"it is a little bit like\na population of predators,"},{"time":449080,"text":"that are so successful in decimating\nthe prey that they must feed on,"},{"time":454560,"text":"that in the end they starve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456720,"text":"Similarly,"},{"time":457960,"text":"the economic sphere has been colonizing\nand cannibalizing the political sphere"},{"time":461680,"text":"to such an extent\nthat it is undermining itself,"},{"time":465080,"text":"causing economic crisis."},{"time":466840,"text":"Corporate power is increasing,"},{"time":468960,"text":"political goods are devaluing,"},{"time":471200,"text":"inequality is rising,"},{"time":473040,"text":"aggregate demand is falling"},{"time":474640,"text":"and CEOs of corporations are too scared\nto invest the cash of their corporations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481520,"text":"So the more capitalism succeeds\nin taking the demos out of democracy,"},{"time":488200,"text":"the taller the twin peaks"},{"time":489560,"text":"and the greater the waste\nof human resources"},{"time":493120,"text":"and humanity's wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495640,"text":"Clearly, if this is right,"},{"time":498520,"text":"we must reunite the political\nand economic spheres"},{"time":501600,"text":"and better do it\nwith a demos being in control,"},{"time":505120,"text":"like in ancient Athens\nexcept without the slaves"},{"time":508080,"text":"or the exclusion of women and migrants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512120,"text":"Now, this is not an original idea."},{"time":513880,"text":"The Marxist left\nhad that idea 100 years ago"},{"time":516679,"text":"and it didn't go very well, did it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518840,"text":"The lesson that we learned\nfrom the Soviet debacle"},{"time":522280,"text":"is that only by a miracle\nwill the working poor be reempowered,"},{"time":528640,"text":"as they were in ancient Athens,"},{"time":530640,"text":"without creating new forms\nof brutality and waste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534960,"text":"But there is a solution:"},{"time":536880,"text":"eliminate the working poor."},{"time":539360,"text":"Capitalism's doing it"},{"time":540640,"text":"by replacing low-wage workers\nwith automata, androids, robots."},{"time":547080,"text":"The problem is"},{"time":548320,"text":"that as long as the economic\nand the political spheres are separate,"},{"time":551560,"text":"automation makes the twin peaks taller,"},{"time":556640,"text":"the waste loftier"},{"time":558400,"text":"and the social conflicts deeper,"},{"time":560480,"text":"including --"},{"time":562320,"text":"soon, I believe --"},{"time":563880,"text":"in places like China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566720,"text":"So we need to reconfigure,"},{"time":569160,"text":"we need to reunite the economic\nand the political spheres,"},{"time":572840,"text":"but we'd better do it\nby democratizing the reunified sphere,"},{"time":578240,"text":"lest we end up with\na surveillance-mad hyperautocracy"},{"time":583960,"text":"that makes The Matrix, the movie,\nlook like a documentary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589600,"text":"So the question is not\nwhether capitalism will survive"},{"time":593040,"text":"the technological innovations\nit is spawning."},{"time":595960,"text":"The more interesting question"},{"time":597600,"text":"is whether capitalism will be succeeded\nby something resembling a Matrix dystopia"},{"time":603360,"text":"or something much closer\nto a Star Trek-like society,"},{"time":607800,"text":"where machines serve the humans"},{"time":610200,"text":"and the humans expend their energies\nexploring the universe"},{"time":614640,"text":"and indulging in long debates\nabout the meaning of life"},{"time":618960,"text":"in some ancient, Athenian-like,\nhigh tech agora."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624360,"text":"I think we can afford to be optimistic."},{"time":629400,"text":"But what would it take,"},{"time":630720,"text":"what would it look like"},{"time":632720,"text":"to have this Star Trek-like utopia,\ninstead of the Matrix-like dystopia?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638240,"text":"In practical terms,"},{"time":639520,"text":"allow me to share just briefly,"},{"time":641280,"text":"a couple of examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643080,"text":"At the level of the enterprise,"},{"time":644880,"text":"imagine a capital market,"},{"time":647240,"text":"where you earn capital as you work,"},{"time":650880,"text":"and where your capital follows you\nfrom one job to another,"},{"time":656240,"text":"from one company to another,"},{"time":657760,"text":"and the company --"},{"time":659040,"text":"whichever one you happen\nto work at at that time --"},{"time":662520,"text":"is solely owned by those who happen\nto work in it at that moment."},{"time":667400,"text":"Then all income stems\nfrom capital, from profits,"},{"time":672120,"text":"and the very concept\nof wage labor becomes obsolete."},{"time":676520,"text":"No more separation between those\nwho own but do not work in the company"},{"time":683160,"text":"and those who work\nbut do not own the company;"},{"time":686440,"text":"no more tug-of-war\nbetween capital and labor;"},{"time":690440,"text":"no great gap between\ninvestment and saving;"},{"time":694600,"text":"indeed, no towering twin peaks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698600,"text":"At the level of the global\npolitical economy,"},{"time":701000,"text":"imagine for a moment"},{"time":702960,"text":"that our national currencies\nhave a free-floating exchange rate,"},{"time":707960,"text":"with a universal,\nglobal, digital currency,"},{"time":711760,"text":"one that is issued\nby the International Monetary Fund,"},{"time":715800,"text":"the G-20,"},{"time":717040,"text":"on behalf of all humanity."},{"time":719600,"text":"And imagine further"},{"time":720840,"text":"that all international trade\nis denominated in this currency --"},{"time":725200,"text":"let's call it \"the cosmos,\""},{"time":727040,"text":"in units of cosmos --"},{"time":729720,"text":"with every government agreeing\nto be paying into a common fund"},{"time":734120,"text":"a sum of cosmos units proportional\nto the country's trade deficit,"},{"time":739680,"text":"or indeed to a country's trade surplus."},{"time":743720,"text":"And imagine that that fund is utilized\nto invest in green technologies,"},{"time":748960,"text":"especially in parts of the world\nwhere investment funding is scarce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754840,"text":"This is not a new idea."},{"time":756440,"text":"It's what, effectively,\nJohn Maynard Keynes proposed"},{"time":759800,"text":"in 1944 at the Bretton Woods Conference."},{"time":764080,"text":"The problem is"},{"time":765320,"text":"that back then, they didn't have\nthe technology to implement it."},{"time":768640,"text":"Now we do,"},{"time":769880,"text":"especially in the context\nof a reunified political-economic sphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776640,"text":"The world that I am describing to you"},{"time":779080,"text":"is simultaneously libertarian,"},{"time":781560,"text":"in that it prioritizes\nempowered individuals,"},{"time":786160,"text":"Marxist,"},{"time":787400,"text":"since it will have confined\nto the dustbin of history"},{"time":790640,"text":"the division between capital and labor,"},{"time":793120,"text":"and Keynesian,"},{"time":795320,"text":"global Keynesian."},{"time":798320,"text":"But above all else,"},{"time":799920,"text":"it is a world in which we will be able\nto imagine an authentic democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805760,"text":"Will such a world dawn?"},{"time":808400,"text":"Or shall we descend\ninto a Matrix-like dystopia?"},{"time":812920,"text":"The answer lies in the political choice\nthat we shall be making collectively."},{"time":817720,"text":"It is our choice,"},{"time":819360,"text":"and we'd better make it democratically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822280,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829480,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Yanis ..."},{"time":831880,"text":"It was you who described yourself\nin your bios as a libertarian Marxist."},{"time":838400,"text":"What is the relevance\nof Marx's analysis today?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"Yanis Varoufakis: Well, if there was\nany relevance in what I just said,"},{"time":845360,"text":"then Marx is relevant."},{"time":846600,"text":"Because the whole point of reunifying\nthe political and economic is --"},{"time":850120,"text":"if we don't do it,"},{"time":851360,"text":"then technological innovation\nis going to create"},{"time":853640,"text":"such a massive fall in aggregate demand,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855960,"text":"what Larry Summers\nrefers to as secular stagnation."},{"time":860760,"text":"With this crisis migrating\nfrom one part of the world,"},{"time":863640,"text":"as it is now,"},{"time":865200,"text":"it will destabilize\nnot only our democracies,"},{"time":867920,"text":"but even the emerging world that is not\nthat keen on liberal democracy."},{"time":872160,"text":"So if this analysis holds water,\nthen Marx is absolutely relevant."},{"time":876000,"text":"But so is Hayek,"},{"time":877760,"text":"that's why I'm a libertarian Marxist,"},{"time":879600,"text":"and so is Keynes,"},{"time":880840,"text":"so that's why I'm totally confused."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"BG: Indeed, and possibly we are too, now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":887400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":889400,"text":"YV: If you are not confused,\nyou are not thinking, OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":892200,"text":"BG: That's a very, very Greek\nphilosopher kind of thing to say --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":895320,"text":"YV: That was Einstein, actually --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897000,"text":"BG: During your talk\nyou mentioned Singapore and China,"},{"time":899640,"text":"and last night at the speaker dinner,"},{"time":901720,"text":"you expressed a pretty strong opinion\nabout how the West looks at China."},{"time":906920,"text":"Would you like to share that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":908520,"text":"YV: Well, there's a great\ndegree of hypocrisy."},{"time":911400,"text":"In our liberal democracies,\nwe have a semblance of democracy."},{"time":915720,"text":"It's because we have confined,\nas I was saying in my talk,"},{"time":918480,"text":"democracy to the political sphere,"},{"time":920160,"text":"while leaving the one sphere\nwhere all the action is --"},{"time":923640,"text":"the economic sphere --"},{"time":924880,"text":"a completely democracy-free zone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927280,"text":"In a sense,"},{"time":928560,"text":"if I am allowed to be provocative,"},{"time":931880,"text":"China today is closer to Britain\nin the 19th century."},{"time":936320,"text":"Because remember,"},{"time":937600,"text":"we tend to associate\nliberalism with democracy --"},{"time":939960,"text":"that's a mistake, historically."},{"time":941480,"text":"Liberalism, liberal,\nit's like John Stuart Mill."},{"time":944040,"text":"John Stuart Mill was particularly\nskeptical about the democratic process."},{"time":948760,"text":"So what you are seeing now in China\nis a very similar process"},{"time":954160,"text":"to the one that we had in Britain\nduring the Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":957360,"text":"especially the transition\nfrom the first to the second."},{"time":960360,"text":"And to be castigating China"},{"time":963680,"text":"for doing that which the West did\nin the 19th century,"},{"time":966840,"text":"smacks of hypocrisy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969520,"text":"BG: I am sure that many people here\nare wondering about your experience"},{"time":973200,"text":"as the Finance Minister of Greece\nearlier this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975960,"text":"YV: I knew this was coming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977365,"text":"BG: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978640,"text":"BG: Six months after,"},{"time":980000,"text":"how do you look back\nat the first half of the year?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":983920,"text":"YV: Extremely exciting,\nfrom a personal point of view,"},{"time":986560,"text":"and very disappointing,"},{"time":987840,"text":"because we had an opportunity\nto reboot the Eurozone."},{"time":991760,"text":"Not just Greece, the Eurozone."},{"time":993880,"text":"To move away from the complacency"},{"time":996840,"text":"and the constant denial\nthat there was a massive --"},{"time":999320,"text":"and there is a massive\narchitectural fault line"},{"time":1002200,"text":"going through the Eurozone,"},{"time":1004400,"text":"which is threatening, massively,\nthe whole of the European Union process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008840,"text":"We had an opportunity\non the basis of the Greek program --"},{"time":1012040,"text":"which by the way,"},{"time":1013400,"text":"was the first program\nto manifest that denial --"},{"time":1017800,"text":"to put it right."},{"time":1019040,"text":"And, unfortunately,"},{"time":1020280,"text":"the powers in the Eurozone,"},{"time":1022120,"text":"in the Eurogroup,"},{"time":1024079,"text":"chose to maintain denial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026079,"text":"But you know what happens."},{"time":1027359,"text":"This is the experience\nof the Soviet Union."},{"time":1029440,"text":"When you try to keep alive"},{"time":1031960,"text":"an economic system\nthat architecturally cannot survive,"},{"time":1036520,"text":"through political will\nand through authoritarianism,"},{"time":1039200,"text":"you may succeed in prolonging it,"},{"time":1040880,"text":"but when change happens"},{"time":1042480,"text":"it happens very abruptly\nand catastrophically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"BG: What kind of change\nare you foreseeing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047031,"text":"YV: Well, there's no doubt"},{"time":1048309,"text":"that if we don't change\nthe architecture of the Eurozone,"},{"time":1051001,"text":"the Eurozone has no future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052920,"text":"BG: Did you make any mistakes\nwhen you were Finance Minister?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1055840,"text":"YV: Every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057080,"text":"BG: For example?\nYV: Anybody who looks back --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064120,"text":"No, but seriously."},{"time":1065520,"text":"If there's any Minister of Finance,\nor of anything else for that matter,"},{"time":1069120,"text":"who tells you after six months in a job,"},{"time":1071360,"text":"especially in such a stressful situation,"},{"time":1075080,"text":"that they have made no mistake,\nthey're dangerous people."},{"time":1077800,"text":"Of course I made mistakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079120,"text":"The greatest mistake\nwas to sign the application"},{"time":1081960,"text":"for the extension of a loan agreement"},{"time":1084080,"text":"in the end of February."},{"time":1085720,"text":"I was imagining"},{"time":1086960,"text":"that there was a genuine interest\non the side of the creditors"},{"time":1089960,"text":"to find common ground."},{"time":1091240,"text":"And there wasn't."},{"time":1092480,"text":"They were simply interested\nin crushing our government,"},{"time":1095120,"text":"just because they did not want"},{"time":1096600,"text":"to have to deal with\nthe architectural fault lines"},{"time":1099760,"text":"that were running through the Eurozone."},{"time":1101800,"text":"And because they didn't want to admit"},{"time":1103640,"text":"that for five years they were implementing\na catastrophic program in Greece."},{"time":1107280,"text":"We lost one-third of our nominal GDP."},{"time":1110200,"text":"This is worse than the Great Depression."},{"time":1112160,"text":"And no one has come clean"},{"time":1113440,"text":"from the troika of lenders\nthat have been imposing this policy"},{"time":1116400,"text":"to say, \"This was a colossal mistake.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1119400,"text":"BG: Despite all this,"},{"time":1120640,"text":"and despite the aggressiveness\nof the discussion,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"you seem to be remaining\nquite pro-European."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1125440,"text":"YV: Absolutely."},{"time":1126680,"text":"Look, my criticism\nof the European Union and the Eurozone"},{"time":1130840,"text":"comes from a person\nwho lives and breathes Europe."},{"time":1135680,"text":"My greatest fear is that\nthe Eurozone will not survive."},{"time":1139280,"text":"Because if it doesn't,"},{"time":1140760,"text":"the centrifugal forces\nthat will be unleashed"},{"time":1143640,"text":"will be demonic,"},{"time":1145360,"text":"and they will destroy the European Union."},{"time":1147360,"text":"And that will be catastrophic\nnot just for Europe"},{"time":1149800,"text":"but for the whole global economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151440,"text":"We are probably the largest\neconomy in the world."},{"time":1155560,"text":"And if we allow ourselves"},{"time":1157320,"text":"to fall into a route\nof the postmodern 1930's,"},{"time":1160160,"text":"which seems to me to be what we are doing,"},{"time":1162840,"text":"then that will be detrimental"},{"time":1164680,"text":"to the future of Europeans\nand non-Europeans alike."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168120,"text":"BG: We definitely hope\nyou are wrong on that point."},{"time":1170560,"text":"Yanis, thank you for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172280,"text":"YV: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173520,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}